---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Kyxel Security Terms of Service"
  description="Review the terms that govern your use of Kyxel Security."
>
  <section class="py-20 bg-[#030417] text-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 space-y-6">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="text-slate-300">Effective: November 2025</p>
      <p class="text-slate-300">
        By using Kyxel Security you agree to abide by applicable laws, keep your credentials secure, and ensure you have rights to monitor the infrastructure you connect.
        Kyxel Security is provided “as is” without warranties; however we aim for 99.9% uptime and proactive support for paid plans.
      </p>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8">Acceptable use</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-300">You may not use Kyxel Security to attack, disrupt or gain unauthorized access to other networks.</p>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8">Termination</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-300">
        You can cancel anytime. We reserve the right to suspend accounts that violate these terms. Questions? Contact <a href="mailto:legal@kyxel.studio" class="text-[#01a1f7] underline">legal@kyxel.studio</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

